 may have given us including any investment preferences andor restrictions tax constraints the tax status of any investment vehicles used and the availability of certain funds or other investments restricted advice we offer restricted advice as defined by the fca which means that that if we recommend an investment solution it will be from one of heartwood investment management’s investment strategies or multiasset funds if based on your personal circumstances it is appropriate for us to advise on pensions or other products outside an investment management relationship we will recommend products chosen from a limited selection of providers that we have selected on the basis of our belief in their quality of service investor protection financial strength and if relevant their financial performance our investment management our investment strategies are offered either as models where you will hold each individual investment within the applicable model or are wrapped within multiasset funds mafs that are managed by heartwood if we believe that one or more of these funds are suitable for you we may hold the funds within a portfolio on your behalf heartwoodmanaged funds in turn may be invested in funds managed by third parties and include investments in other asset classes selected by us from the whole of the market compensation we are covered by the financial services compensation scheme clients may be entitled to compensation from the scheme if heartwood wealth management limited cannot meet its obligations this depends on the type of business and the circumstances of the claim most types of investment business are covered for 00 of the first £ for further information about compensation arrangements is available from the financial services compensation scheme residence the pages on this site are prepared and issued in the united kingdom and are intended for the information of united kingdom residents only in particular the information on this site is not for distributio